items.name: Bliss-Engine
items.description: The Bliss engine is a 2D/3D game engine using LWJGL 2.9.3. This engine is written in Java and uses OpenGL. This engine is under the MIT License free for anyone to use, modify, and do as they please. This project is for me to learn how game engines work including physics, graphics, and other aspects of engines.

items.name: stashbox
items.description: Stashbox is a lightweight Python library designed for minimalistic data storage and retrieval. It allows you to easily stash (store) and fetch (retrieve) data with support for optional persistence, compression, expiry, and logging.
